==========================================================================================
Section 1 : Information regarding the producer_consumer_v1.0 structure.
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
include/       --> consists of header files
src/           --> contains Makefile and main file
README -       --> Gives quick information regarding Package and how to execute 
                   the code.
lib/	       --> contains file having function definitions.


=============================================================================================
Section 2 : Steps for using  producer_consumer_v1.0
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Copy the "producer_consumer_v1.0.tar". Untar the file using
         $tar -xvf producer_consumer_v1.0.tar

in your home directory. This will create folder "producer_consumer_v1.0"

The following directory structure of producer_consumer_v1.0. will be created in the
main directory i.e "producer_consumer_v1.0".
    
	  /include        /src          /lib


==============================================================================================
Section 3 : Pre-Requisites.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TBB2.0 should be installed and configured with Linux /Unix OS.

===============================================================================================
Section 4 : Steps for compiling producer_consumer_v1.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Go in the respective directory
and give
         make


===============================================================================================
Section 5 : Steps for executing producer_consumer_v1.0
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

        ./name_of_executable #Numberofthreads,#NumberofItems, #NumberofProducers, #NumberofConsumers


